<entry code="DQC.US.0043.7488" level="error">
 <message filing_url="http://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1936756/000119983526000138/nbh-s1a.htm" severity="error" effectiveDate="2018-06-01" cid="2480908284176">[DQC.US.0043.7488] The concept IncreaseDecreaseInOtherAssetRelatedParty is included in the calculation of NetCashProvidedByUsedInOperatingActivities. This is in the role 00000006 - Statement - CONDENSED CONSOLIDATED STATEMENTS OF CASH FLOWS (Unaudited). IncreaseDecreaseInOtherAssetRelatedParty is a debit balance type concept representing a natural cash inflow in the reconciliation of net income (loss) to NetCashProvidedByUsedInOperatingActivities.
A debit balance type concept should always be assigned a positive one (+1) calculation weight as it is an addition to net income (loss) to reconcile to NetCashProvidedByUsedInOperatingActivities. IncreaseDecreaseInOtherAssetRelatedParty has been incorrectly provided a negative one (-1) calculation weight in the extension taxonomy. 
Correct the calculation weight to positive one (+1) and input the value as a positive amount if it is an addition of a non-cash expense or loss, a decrease in an asset, or an increase in a liability. If the value is an increase in an asset or a decrease in a liability and IncreaseDecreaseInOtherAssetRelatedParty is the correct concept, input a negative value.   

Rule Element Id:7488
Rule version: 30.0.0RC1 - nbh-s1a.htm 918</message>
